-- Brazil Central Bank Sees 2011 CPI Rising at 4.6% in Reference Scenario
-- B y   I u r i   D a n t a s   a n d   M a t t h e w   B r i s t o w
-- 2010-09-30T11:31:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-30/brazil-central-bank-sees-2011-cpi-rising-at-4-6-in-reference-scenario.html
Brazilian  consumer  prices will rise
5.0 percent in 2010 and 4.6 percent in 2011, according to the
central bank’s reference scenario, published today in the bank’s
quarterly inflation report posted on its website.  The bank forecast gross domestic product will grow 7.3
percent this year.  To contact the reporters on this story:
